Function DESTROY-THREAD

Syntax:

  destroy-thread thread => interrupt

Arguments and Values:

  thread - a thread.
  interrupt - an interrupt of type DESTRUCTION-INTERRUPT.

Description:

  Creates an interrupt of type DESTRUCTION-INTERRUPT, adds it to the thread's
  pending interrupt list, and then returns it. If the interrupt is serviced, the
  thread will be aborted.

  A call to DESTROY-THREAD synchronizes-with any signaling of the interrupt in
  the thread.

Exceptional Situations:

  If the thread is no longer alive, an error of type THREAD-DEAD is signaled.

Notes:

  (defun destroy-thread (thread)
    (interrupt-thread thread 'destruction-interrupt))
